Airports Company South Africa&rsquo;s (ACSA&rsquo;s) airport charges will be reduced by 35.5% for the 2017/18 financial year. Airport charges will then rise by 5.8% in the 2018/19 financial year and 7.4% in the 2019/20 financial year. Passenger service charges per departing domestic passenger will be R82, passenger service charges per departing passenger for an airport within Botswana, Lesotho, Namibia or Swaziland will be R169 and passenger service charges per departing international passenger will be R223. &nbsp;&nbsp; &ldquo;We are happy that this process has finally concluded and all role-players in the industry can now have regulatory certainty,&rdquo; says ACSA CEO Bongani Maseko.